# Fluff Date: 2026-02-28 16:30:01
<overview>
<p>The Aesir is an assault DropShip developed by Clan Ghost Bear during the Jihad as one half of a matched escort pair alongside its sister design, the Vanir. Produced at multiple Clan naval installations, the Aesir entered service in the late 3070s as a dedicated aerospace fighter carrier. Where the Vanir focused on fleet missile defense, the Aesir was designed to project offensive aerospace power, providing combat air patrols and strike capability for convoys and the diminished Ghost Bear WarShip fleet. The class has remained in limited production as a cornerstone of the Rasalhague Dominion's naval doctrine.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>The Aesir is an 18,000-ton military spheroid optimized for fighter deployment operations. Its primary combat contribution comes from its extensive aerospace fighter bays, allowing the vessel to serve as a mobile launch platform for strike missions and defensive screens. The hull mounts a comprehensive weapons suite including sub-capital missile launchers, HAG 40 batteries, ATM 12 racks, ER PPCs, and Large Pulse Lasers, providing layered defensive fire while its fighter complement engages hostile vessels. Ninety tons of Ferro-Aluminum armor concentrated on the nose and flanks gives the Aesir substantial survivability against incoming fire, though its aft arc remains comparatively vulnerable. The drive system provides adequate acceleration to maintain formation with most military convoys while retaining enough agility to reposition during fleet actions. As a carrier design, the Aesir deliberately trades direct engagement firepower for force multiplication, relying on its embarked fighter wings to project offensive power at range while the mothership maintains a defensive posture behind its escort screen. Anti-missile systems provide point defense against incoming ordnance.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>The standard Aesir serves as the primary aerospace fighter carrier for the Ghost Bear touman's naval forces, pairing with the missile defense-oriented Vanir to form a complementary escort package. Together, the two classes provide both offensive aerospace strike capability and defensive missile screening for high-value convoys and surviving WarShip assets.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The Aesir was born from necessity during the Jihad, when Word of Blake space forces inflicted severe losses on Clan Ghost Bear's naval assets. Ghost Bear naval planners recognized that replacing their lost WarShips was impractical in the near term and instead developed the Aesir and Vanir as a cost-effective escort solution that could be produced in greater numbers. The two designs shared common hull elements and systems to simplify logistics, while specializing in complementary roles.</p><p>Production commenced at two shipyards, with Alshain Naval Yards handling the primary production run while Gorton, Kingsley and Thorpe Enterprises on Rasalhague provided additional capacity. The Aesir saw its first combat deployments escorting supply convoys through contested space lanes during the final years of the Jihad, where its fighter wings proved effective at deterring Blakist raiding forces.</p><p>Following the establishment of the Rasalhague Dominion, the Aesir remained in limited production to maintain the Dominion's naval capabilities. The class saw action during the Second Combine-Dominion War beginning in 3100, where its fighter wings provided aerospace superiority during planetary assault operations. While never produced in large numbers, the Aesir has proven a reliable and effective fleet asset, with active examples serving primarily in the Dominion's frontline naval formations.</p>
</history>

